description: From Middle English somdel, sumdel (“somewhat, to an extent, in some measure; part, portion, a bit, small amount; in ~ this instance, this case”), equivalent to some +‎ deal.

entries.meaning: (obsolete or dialect) In some measure or degree; somewhat, partly, partially
examples: In Ethiopia all the rivers and all the waters be trouble, and they be somedeal salt for the great heat that is there.
